    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect function signatures in test_logmap8 causing unexpected behavior\n\n### Summary\nThe `test_logmap8()` function in the LTE testbench was calling `dlsch_encoding()` and `dlsch_decoding()` with incorrect parameter orders, causing unexpected behavior when running the test. Additionally, the `frame` variable was referenced but never declared.\n\nThis fix corrects the function calls to match the actual function signatures and adds the missing variable declaration.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/TESTBENCH/ltetest.c`: \n  - Added missing `frame` variable declaration\n  - Fixed `dlsch_encoding()` function call to match correct signature\n  - Fixed `dlsch_decoding()` function call to match correct signature\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running the ltetest executable, the test would not behave as expected due to the mismatched function calls. The dlsch_encoding and dlsch_decoding functions would receive parameters in incorrect positions, leading to undefined behavior during the LTE downlink shared channel processing simulation.\n"
}